# Story 3.1: Display Train Positions on Map

## Story Metadata
- **Epic:** 3 - Map & Fleet Visualization
- **Status:** done
- **Implemented:** 2025-12-28
- **Session:** SESSION-004, SESSION-005

## User Story
As **Diana (Dispatcher)**,
I want **to see train positions on an interactive map**,
So that **I can visualize fleet distribution geographically**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status |
|----|----------|--------|
| AC1 | Map displays Portugal railway network area | PASS |
| AC2 | Train markers show on map | PASS |
| AC3 | Map is interactive (pan, zoom) | PASS |
| AC4 | Map loads in < 5 seconds | PASS |

## Implementation Details

### Files Created
- `apps/web/src/components/map/FleetMap.tsx` - Leaflet map component

### Technical Decisions
- **Vanilla Leaflet** instead of react-leaflet (SSR compatibility)
- OpenStreetMap tiles for free, reliable mapping
- Marker clustering for performance with 100+ trains

### Bug Fix (SESSION-005)
Original react-leaflet had SSR issues ("render is not a function").
Replaced with vanilla Leaflet using useRef/useEffect pattern.

## Dev Notes
Map centered on Portugal (lat: 39.5, lon: -8.0).
Initial zoom level shows all depots and major routes.

